Meet <b>Katie Jackson</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Katie Jackson lives at 38258 Strawberry Way in one of Ravenwood's old-fashioned, elegant estates.  Katie Jackson has been hard at work modernizing and redesigning her home since she moved in on March 30, 2005, and she's finally found a way to balance her hip tastes with the historical style of her neighborhood.<br><br>Since moving to Millsberry, Katie Jackson has really made a mark on the town's athletic scene.  She's very sporty and will give any game or competition a try.  Because Katie Jackson is so flexible, she has a wide range of skills that allow her to excel at almost every game she tries.  One look at Katie Jackson's trophy shelf is all it takes to see that she's a very formidable athlete!  Katie Jackson's favorite sport, though, is basketball.  She loves driving to the hoop for a layup, directing complex defensive plays, or sometimes just practicing her three-point shots.<br><br>When she's not on the court, Katie Jackson enjoys hanging out at the mall with her friends.  She especially likes to visit the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Clothing Store</a>, where she is always sure to try on the hottest fashions in her favorite shades of pink, black, and green.  Katie Jackson loves to look stylish &mdash; even her workout clothes are fashionable!  <br><br>Katie Jackson also likes spending time with her friends at an ice cream parlor or just hanging out at her best friend's house.  Some of Katie Jackson's fondest memories are of afternoons spent at her best friend's house, simply listening to the latest pop, punk, and rap releases while talking about a variety of subjects, ranging from animals to the Millsberry Millers.<br><br>Thank you for being a fine citizen, Katie Jackson, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
